Project Overview:
I want to build a micro-jobs marketplace website (similar to Fiverr / TaskRabbit style) where employers can post jobs and candidates can view/apply. The key feature is that candidates must subscribe (paid membership) to see full job details.

Core Requirements:
1. User Roles & Access
• Employers: Can register, post jobs, and manage listings.
• Candidates: Can register, browse jobs, but need subscription to view full details & apply.
• Admin: Approve jobs, manage users, manage subscriptions.
2. Candidate Dashboard
• Profile management (basic info, photo, contact).
• Subscription status (active/expired).
• Job applications history.
3. Employer Dashboard
• Post and manage jobs.
• Track candidate applications.
• Option to feature or highlight jobs (extra monetisation).
4. Subscription System
• Multiple plans (monthly, quarterly, yearly).
• Auto-renewal & expiry handling.
• Payment integration: Stripe, Razorpay, PayPal.
5. Job Listings
• Job categories, filters, search.
• Non-subscribers: can see only job title + basic info.
• Subscribers: full job description + apply option.
6. Other Features
• Mobile-responsive, clean UI.
• Secure login/registration with email or mobile OTP.
• Notifications (email + optional WhatsApp).
• Scalable for future features (wallet, chat, reviews, etc.).

